<@U340CHVJA>, I wanted to qualify something I said the other day about where I build my decks digitally. Someone was commenting that deckstats is unwieldy, and it is, but I use it because I build my decks pretty much exclusively in Cockatrice, and then I can automatically export it to tappedout or deckstats. Since the deck is already put in for me, I think deckstats offers more analytically, but in terms of input, tappedout is superior.
I actually build mine initially on mtgvault
I've never heard of it.
It's so much faster than tapped. When I'm at a set 100 I move to tappedout, but mtgvault is so much faster for adding/removing
Cockatrice is the fastest I've found, and exporting a deck takes seconds.
It's nice because you have the client on your computer, it's not a website.
Good point, maybe next time I rough one out I'll try cockatrice
my initial scrape for edhrec was mtgvault
i think i got like 900 dekcs or something
Definitely try it out, Dana.
The site has had bugs that have existed for years, and they are sometimes weeks behind gatherer for updating card pools.
